<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 2:12PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
southern Summers, northeastern Mercer and southwestern Monroe
Counties through 245 PM EDT...
At 212 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lerona, or near Athens, moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Hinton...
Athens...
Pipestem...
Camp Creek...
Red Sulphur Spring...
Buck...
and Elgood.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
